  "content_id": "0cb284f1-1b67-43b7-b947-5b57a8dd6e48",
  "description": "Tax and reporting rules for employers paying income tax on a directors' behalf",
  "details": {
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "hide_chapter_navigation": false,
    "parts": [
      {
        "body": "<p>As an employer paying income tax on behalf of company directors, you have certain National Insurance and reporting obligations.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"whats-included\">What’s included</h2>\n\n<p>If you pay a company director without deducting tax under <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>, and HM Revenue and Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) then recovers the unpaid tax from you, this counts as a benefit.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "overview",
        "title": "Overview"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You might not have to report or pay anything to HM Revenue and Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) if the director doesn’t have a ‘material interest’ in your company, and either of the following applies:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>they’re a full-time working director</li>\n  <li>your company is a charity or not-for-profit organisation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>In broad terms, a director has a material interest in a company if they (alone or together with associates) own or can control more than 5% of its ordinary share capital. This is explained in more detail in the <a href=\"/expenses-benefits-income-tax-paid-directors-behalf/technical-guidance\">technical guidance</a>.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "whats-exempt",
        "title": "What's exempt"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>If the income tax you pay on a director’s behalf isn’t <a href=\"/expenses-benefits-income-tax-paid-directors-behalf/whats-exempt\">exempt</a>, you’ll need to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>report on form P11D</li>\n  <li>add the <a href=\"/expenses-benefits-income-tax-paid-directors-behalf/work-out-the-value\">value of the benefit</a> to the director’s earnings when deducting and paying Class 1 National Insurance (but not <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax) through your payroll</li>\n</ul>\n\n",
        "slug": "what-to-report-and-pay",
        "title": "What to report and pay"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>Use the amount of tax recovered from you by HM Revenue and Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>), minus any amount paid back to you (‘made good’) by the director.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "work-out-the-value",
        "title": "Work out the value"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>The following guides contain more detailed information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim21790.htm\"><abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax not deducted from director’s earnings</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/nimmanual/nim02370.htm\">Class 1 National Insurance contributions: earnings of employees and office holders</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/EIM20212.htm\">the meaning of ‘material interest’ in a company</a></p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n",
        "slug": "technical-guidance",
        "title": "Technical guidance"
      }
    ]
  },
